## §10 — Anti-Regression Rules

> ⚠️ This section supersedes the legacy `## NEVER do` block below.
> Do not remove that block.

- `context.chat_data` is **PROHIBITED** — Render is stateless; use `system_state` table.
- No `asyncio.sleep()` inside handlers.
- `disable_web_page_preview=True` on every message that contains an inline URL.
- `query.answer()` must **always** be the first line of every callback handler.
- All `url=` values must start with `https://`.

## NEVER do

- Do not mix ParseMode.HTML and ParseMode.MARKDOWN in the same message —
  pick HTML and escape dynamic content with html.escape() where needed
- Do not rewrite entire keyboards.py, callbacks.py or handlers.py
- Do not remove any existing command handler (/ask /proposal /governance /govlist /govhistory /govstatus /vote /delegate /revoke /setwallet /premium /confirmpayment /start /help)
- Do not rename the `menu:digest` callback even if the button label changes to "Intelligence Signals"
- Do not remove /confirmpayment handler even after PaymentPoller is active
- Do not use context.chat_data for persistent state
- Do not run uvicorn in the same async thread as PTB
- Do not display Portuguese text to the bot user (English only)

