## §19 — message.text Matching Anti-Pattern

Telegram's `message.text` always returns **plain text** — HTML tags are stripped.

**CORRECT:**
```python
is_settings_root = "⚙️ Settings" in message_text
is_wallet_menu   = "Set Wallet" in message_text
```

**WRONG — always evaluates to False:**
```python
is_settings_root = message_text.startswith("<b>⚙️ Settings</b>")
```

This rule applies to every screen detection in `_refresh_keyboard_after_preference_change`
and any future function that inspects `message.text` to determine current screen context.

